Therefore, this issue could be similar/duplicate to other freeze issues e.g. keyboard layout/ime changing, xdotool key with unicode character, setxkbmap. They all introduce freezes in gnome.

This works for me, replacing existing method in desktopManager.js.  Tested on 2 monitors with enough files to overfill both.

```
    _addFileItemCloseTo(item) {
        let [x, y] = (item.savedCoordinates == null) ? [0, 0] : item.savedCoordinates;
        let monitorIndex = findMonitorIndexForPos(x, y);

        let monitorIndices = Object.keys(this._desktopGrids);
        while (monitorIndex != monitorIndices[0]) {
            monitorIndices.unshift(monitorIndices.pop());
        }
        for (let i = 0; i < monitorIndices.length; i++) {
            let desktopGrid = this._desktopGrids[i];
            try {
                desktopGrid.addFileItemCloseTo(item, x, y);
                i = monitorIndices.length;
            } catch (e) {
                if (i == monitorIndices.length - 1) {
                    log(`Error adding children to desktop: ${e.message}`);
                }
                log(`Got error adding children to desktop, but have another monitor to check: ${e.message}`);
            }
        }
    }
```

